I built a mean-reversion strategy on BTCUSD in TradingView using Pine Script.

For entries I used two IF/THEN conditions with technical indicators:

IF RSI(14) < 30 AND price is below the lower Bollinger Band
→ THEN enter a long position.

IF RSI(14) > 70 AND price is above the upper Bollinger Band
→ THEN enter a short position.

For exits I used:

IF I’m long and RSI > 50 OR price crosses back above the middle Bollinger Band
→ THEN close the long.

IF I’m short and RSI < 50 OR price crosses back below the middle Bollinger Band
→ THEN close the short.

To meet the requirement of at least 500 trades, I ran the strategy on BTCUSD, 10-second timeframe, over the available data window (Feb 16–23, 2026). That produced:

Total trades: 1,181

Profitable trades: 710 / 1,181 (≈ 60.1%)
